<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>It would be helpful to have hooks in Zend_Mail such that child classes only need to implement init() (called from parent::__construct()) and perhaps _preSend() (called as the first line of parent::send())</p>

<p>This would allow users to do some trivial setup, for instance adding a default BCC to every outgoing mail, without worrying about overriding core functions.</p>

